bundle.name: Qlik Dashboard bundle
bundle.description:
This is a set of supported objects that will facilitate dashboard creation in Qlik Sense: A date picker, a variable input, a demand-reporting button and a share button. These can be used in addition to the objects found under "Charts".

For limitations and support conditions, see the documentation.

qAttributeExpressions.qExpression: pick(match(v_ViewUptake, 'NFIRST', 'NSECOND', 'NADD'),[TG - # Dose First administered],[TG - # Full vaccination], [TG - # Dose Additional])
qAttributeExpressions.qLabelExpression:
=pick(match(v_ViewUptake, 'NFIRST', 'NSECOND', 'NADD'), 'N. first doses administered', 'N. primary courses administered', 'N. boostet/additional doses' )
& ' in '  &pick(match(v_ViewTargetGroup, '50', '60', '70', '80', 'HCW', 'LTCF'), '50+', '60+', '70+', '80+', 'HCW', 'LTCF')

qFieldDefs:

aggr(only({1<EU27_EEA=P(EU27_EEA), [UptakeAdd_$(v_ViewTargetGroup)]={">0"}>}[Member State]), [Member State])
)

qAttributeExpressions.qExpression:
pick(match(v_ViewUptake & '_' & v_ViewTargetGroup, 
'FIRST_80', 'SECOND_80', 'FIRST_HCW', 'SECOND_HCW', 'FIRST_LTCF', 'SECOND_LTCF', 
'NFIRST_80', 'NSECOND_80', 'NFIRST_HCW', 'NSECOND_HCW', 'NFIRST_LTCF', 'NSECOND_LTCF'),
	//Uptake	
      num(rangemin(1,sum({1} Uptake1st_80)),'0.0%;-0.0%;Not reported'),
      num(rangemin(1,sum({1} Uptake2nd_80)),'0.0%;-0.0%;Not reported'),
      num(rangemin(1,sum({1} Uptake1st_HCW)),'0.0%;-0.0%;Not reported'),
      num(rangemin(1,sum({1} Uptake2nd_HCW)),'0.0%;-0.0%;Not reported'),
      num(rangemin(1,sum({1} Uptake1st_LTCF)),'0.0%;-0.0%;Not reported'),
      num(rangemin(1,sum({1} Uptake2nd_LTCF)),'0.0%;-0.0%;Not reported'),    	
	//Doses
      num(sum({1} Dose1st_80),'#,##0;-#,##0;Not reported'),
      num(sum({1} Dose2nd_80),'#,##0;-#,##0;Not reported'),
      num(sum({1} Dose1st_HCW),'#,##0;-#,##0;Not reported'),
      num(sum({1} Dose2nd_HCW),'#,##0;-#,##0;Not reported'),
      num(sum({1} Dose1st_LTCF),'#,##0;-#,##0;Not reported'),
      num(sum({1} Dose2nd_LTCF),'#,##0;-#,##0;Not reported')
)
